This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with reinforcement learning, a subfield of AI. The paper also discusses the use of causal models to explain the behaviour of reinforcement learning agents, which is a topic of interest in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the study conducted in the paper involves human participants, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to generate explanations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the study involves a real-time strategy game, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
